# HTML-PDF Converter

POC: A lambda-like function should be able to create a PDF file with dynamic data.

This uses `puppeteer` to create the PDF file based on an HTML template, which uses `ejs` to handle dynamic data injections.

This is intended to be used as a lambda-like function which expects an event with the following parameters to be passed in:

```ts
interface IEvent {
  template: Template;
  payload: any;
}
```

Once successful, it returns the following:

```ts
interface ISuccessResponse {
  data: string; // File as a Base64 encoded string
  mimeType: "application/pdf";
  extension: ".pdf";
}
```

In order to prevent creating a file in storage, the following in `handler.ts` can be modified:

```ts
// Download the PDF
const pdf = await page.pdf({
  /**
   * NOTE: Remove `path` to prevent creating a file in storage.
   */
  path: join(
    __dirname,
    `../.temp/${Math.round(new Date().getTime() / 1000)}-${template}_${
      crypto.randomUUID().split("-")[0]
    }.pdf`
  ),
  margin: { top: "100px", right: "50px", bottom: "100px", left: "50px" },
  printBackground: true,
  format: "A4",
});
```

## Caveats

### CSS

CSS styling needs to be defined in the `<style>` tag rather than being loaded directly from a stylesheet file.

### Images

Loading images from files is not supported. They need to be loaded in Base64 encoding when being used inside the HTML body or the `<style>` tags.

#### Images inside HTML files

```html
<img
  src="data:image/png;base64,"
  alt="Hobbiton Door"
/>
```

The above snippet loads the following image: <img
  src="data:image/png;base64,"
  alt="Hobbiton Door"
  height="100"
  align="middle"
/>

#### Images inside CSS

```css
body {
  background-image: url("data:image/jpeg;base64,");
}
```

This snippet an be used to load the following image as the background of the `<body>`:

<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," />

### Custom Fonts

Custom fonts need to be imported as Base64 inside the styles. The following snippet will be helpful.

```css
@font-face {
  font-family: "Shadows Into Light Two";
  src: url(data:font/truetype;charset=utf-8;base64,)
    format("truetype");
}

.signature {
  font-family: "Shadows Into Light Two";
}
```
